ry60003333:

Ok, the code in the compiler and the file don’t match. In the compiler, your missing the () after the method name, but they exist in the file. Try compiling again or something.

He’s highlighted the wrong thing.
Look at the method above, no parenthesis.

Change the

public void chrisminifinish {

to:

public void chrisminifinish() {

Conventionally speaking, it should be chrisMiniFinish(), but I didn’t want to make you try and call a method that doesn’t exist (even wrong capitalization will toss you an error :()
